claims:
1. A method of differentiating hematopoietic stem cells (HSC) into mature natural killer (NK) cells, said method comprising the steps of:
a) providing isolated HSCs;
b) culturing said cells of step a) in medium containing thrombopoietin (TPO), stem cell factor (SCF) and FMS-like tyrosine kinase 3 ligand (FLT3-L);
c) transfecting and/or transducing said cells of step b) with at least one transcription factor selected from the list comprising: T-Box expressed in T cells (T-BET) or Eomesodermin (EOMES); or a combination thereof;
d) culturing the cells obtained from step c) in a medium containing at least one cytokine selected from the list comprising IL-2 or IL-15; preferably IL-15;
whereby said mature NK cells are obtainable from day 3 after the start of step d).
